======================================================================
PART 3: PATH REVERSAL AND MOD-4 STRUCTURE
======================================================================
T and T^op always have the same H (path reversal).
No labeled tournament equals its complement (n≥2).
So tournaments pair up: N/2 pairs with H(T)=H(T^op).
This is consistent with 3/4 ratio but doesn't prove it.

